The design of the Aqueous Ammonia System is to the recognized and generally accepted good engineering practice using corrosion-resistance materials that are compatible with NH4OH.  Select safety features include the following:

a. Continuous monitoring of critical process parameters by the Control Room (e.g., pressure, temperature, liquid flow, leak detection, etc.); 

b. Stainless steel pipeline withing secondary containment piping with continuous leak detection monitoring of the annular space for the UST and pipeline segments outside the power blocks; 

c. Pressure relief valve (PRV) on the UST and supply pump discharge piping;

d. UST equipped with flame arrestor, vacuum breaker, and overfill alarm;

e. Ammonia vapor detectors located at the UST area, along the Units 3 & 4 Pipeline, and at the Units 3 & 4 SCR Skids that will alarm in the Control Room.



Detailed system descriptions, plans, procedures and training are available to the operators and maintenance personnel to ensure the consistent, accurate and safe operation.  New system descriptions, plans, procedures and training for the ESEC Modifications are under development and will be complete prior to the startup of the new equipment.  



